Variance explained

Using an independent replication allows unbiased estimate of phenotypic variance explained

The cumulative plot shows variance explained in various percentages of DNA methylation sites. 99 % of the cis associations explain less than 0.2094 and 99% of the trans associations explain less than 0.1552 of the variance.

How does the SNP h2 (estimated in ARIES) relate to the variance explained by clumped SNPs (Generation Scotland)

Use Van Dongen heritability estimates using twins

  • There are 411169 CpGs with significant h2 estimates in van Dongen.
  • 118955 were present in the GS replication dataset
